outputs.output_descr:
The project "Developing the Capacity of National Parliaments to prevent Conflict and Armed Violence and To Restore Community Security" is a joint BDP/DGG (GPPS)  BCPR initiative. The work-plan for 2010 builds on global activities launched in 2009 and requests from colleagues in country offices to address CPR and PD issues that were discussed at a dedicated CPR and PD day at the PD Community of Practice (December 2009). In 2010, focus will be on regional activities, addressing sensitive post-conflict issues in two regions through the working group methodology, namely:  
-	Launching two working groups (Arab States Region and Central America):
	Start the knowledge building, baselines, and identification of relevant topic for one working group per region;
	Prepare comparative studies, establish benchmarks, identify core participants
-	Continuing the parliamentary development knowledge building and dissemination efforts on dedicated CPR and Human and Community Security issues;
-	Strengthening established partnerships with national parliaments, and increase level of collaboration with other UNDP regional and national projects, and with national organizations and agencies working in parliamentary development in the two regions.
